Crazy it’s been a month since we got engaged!! In a few months, I’ll no longer be a Ms but a Mrs 🥰 2023 is going to be filled with so many first and beautiful memories. I love you with all my heart. I can’t wait @tinfoiltaco 
.
.
.
#engaged #engaged2023 #2023bride #ftworth #thecolonytx #weddingseason #fortworthtx #hoteldrover #2023isouryear

Today is the day I get to marry the man of my dreams…literally! Growing up a girl always dreams about her wedding day. Although the man in my dreams I could never make out his face or knew his name. Not until a several months before I met Eric. I was having dreams of my wedding day. I could see a shadow of the man I would marry. I saw a tall, dark headed, bearded man. Couldn’t make out anymore features but just make out a blur. The name I would hear over and over was Eric. Fast forward to meeting Eric, I didn’t put 2 in 2 together until I started falling in love with him. I knew in May after we started dating I was going to marry him. He is truly the Man I’ve prayed for and dreamed about. I’m so blessed and honored to become his wife today.

Baby Freideman coming in August!!!

Eric and I are over the moon excited for our new addition to our little family. Biscuit, I know will be the best big brother ever. Baby Freideman is expected to be here late August. Motherhood has always been something I’ve wanted. As some of Yall know, it was something that I thought I would never get to experience. The Good Lord had his plan all along and I can’t wait to meet our miracle baby. 2023 has truly been a whirlwind and continues to be the best year ever. We are blessed beyond measure! I pray we are half the parents, that our parents were to us. 
#baby #babyannouncement #comingaugust2023 #miraclebaby #bigbrother #englishbulldog #englishbulldogsofig #englishbulldogsofinstagram #dogbigbrother

Happy 1 Month Anniversary @tinfoiltaco 🤣😘 

Our wedding day will be something I’ll cherish for the rest of my life. Even tho it was small, it was intimate and everything I’ve ever dreamed of. Excited for many amazing more years. Ready to celebrate next year with our little girl and many more friends and family.

Scottie Jo you are already loved and adored by so many. The last week has been filled with so many emotions. I never felt so scared in my life but I know you needed to be here to continue your fight. The fight that we all saw the moment you entered into this world. Feisty, sassy and letting the world know you have arrived. Born 10 weeks early, we have a long road ahead. I know the Good Lord will be by our side and continue to guide us. Happy Birthday my sweet baby girl. Your Dad and I are ready to celebrate this life with you.

NICU life, what can I say BESIDES the days went fast but the time was slow. It’s like running in a nightmare and only staying in one spot. You are just trying to wake up and want it to end. The day I was discharged from the hospital, was one of the hardest days of my life.  It was like I abandoned her. That I was the biggest failure and the guilt when I had to leave her was unbearable. Sure not every day was bad but every day had a sense of worry. A worry that continues when you finally walk your final steps out of the NICU pod. Praying that you never have to go back or see the walls of a hospital in that capacity ever again. Not everyone has or will understand your struggles but prayers from others has made it easier to cope. I learned a lot about myself and how to be the best mother for my daughter. My wonderful husband has been our biggest cheerleader and supporter. Always letting me cry it out and express my worries. We are FINALLY home and I thank God for all the blessings he continues to shine on us. The most graceful and biggest thank you to the NICU team at Texas Health of Plano. They truly took the best care of SJ. Each day was a challenge for us but they worked with us to make sure we had everything we needed to bring her home. Not to mention the compassion they had for our little girl. Lastly, thank you all for the prayers, love and support. We couldn’t have made it without Y’all. 53 days down but a lifetime of loving you, Scottie Jo! 

#nicubaby #nicu #niculife #nicugraduate #nicuwarrior #nicujourney #preemiestrong #preemiestrong #preemiebaby #preemiemom

Happy 2 months Scottie!

In the last 2 months you have overcome so many obstacles and we couldn’t be more proud. You are determined, eager and FULL of sass! 

Few things she enjoys:
- giving you the sided eye 
- Love car rides (basically anything with movement)
- Hit or mess on tummy time
- Loves to roll from stomach to back during tummy time
- Already assisting holding her own bottle 
- Loves water pouring on her during spa days

*swipe to see the melt day that ended our 1 minute photo shoot 🤣 @tinfoiltaco

Happy 3 months SJ! 🧡

We are both so proud of how far you have come. “Technically” you are 3 weeks old but you would never know it. Feels like we will be 1 before we know it 😭 although I already have planned out her first birthday party…definitely not ready for it. Time needs to slow down. 

SJ has grown 1.25lb in 2 week, which is crazy. We are having a great time enjoying our first football season together. She is getting more aware of biscuit and I just LOVE that. 

We are excited to celebrate Longhorn Friday on 3 months 🤘🏻🧡🏈 we are working on her hook ‘em horn #longhornfriday #burntorangefriday #texaslonghorns #texasfootball

Finally sharing Scottie’s room. I’ve had several people ask and you know how mom life is. BUSY! Crazy saying that, especially when you do have time. All you want to do is relax or take a nap 🤣 #nursery #babygirl #babynursery #babynurserydecor #firsttimemom #firsttimemum

4 months today. Swipe to see the “Baby in a pumpkin”trend …aka… DISASTER!! 🤣🧡 I am so happy I got SJ and Biscuit together. So wild she is 4 months. Time flies and we are loving every day with our babies.

Of course we had to do a costumes from a classic and 1 of my favorite movies. Happy 1st Halloween Scottie Jo…I mean Lieutenant Dan 🤣 #forrestgump #halloween #halloweencostume #firsthalloween #lieutenantdan #ltdan

When you fall in love with the viral Home Depot tree. Yes I know I already have several trees and don’t need it BUT this tree is breathtaking. The video doesn’t do it justice. I’m so glad we got it before Halloween and it was the last one.

Happy 5 months to my little turkey 🦃 I still can’t get over how big you have gotten. We truly are blessed for a clean bill of health. You continue to surprise us daily and your smile melts our hearts. Your laugh is like music to my soul. We love you so much. Happy 1st Thanksgiving.

It wouldn’t be a milestone picture without a meltdown but gosh I love it. Happy 1/2 Birthday Scottie!! Truly can’t get over how much you’ve grown. Everyday I’m surprised by you. You are a chatty Cathy and I’m ready for you to start talking to me any minute. We love you so much and you have made this the best Christmas ever.

IT GETS BETTER!

As the year ends, thinking back to prior years and it did get better! There’s been so many times in the last 2 years that I’ve wanted to hug that 34 year old me. Shout, even that 27 year old me. Just to say “IT GETS BETTER.” I know I’ve had a bumpy, long and stressful road. For years and years I’ve shed so many tears and never thought I would be where I am today. Married to an amazing man who loves, adores and supports me in every way possible. Our little girl, who has started the family I’ve always wanted. Whom I adore and cherish so much. A career that I love but mostly importantly, my faith. It has strengthened and I’ve learned to put my trust into him. I want to pinch myself to make sure I’m not dreaming anymore. Every day that goes by I thank God for letting me put faith into his hands and letting him control my outcome. At the end of the day, all what I have is because of his grace. I’ve learned a lot from the past and couldn’t be more happier with my life he has given me. 

At the end of the day, if you feel defeated…just remember this will pass and it will GET BETTER!!!
